eventsAnnotated.name: 2013 Australia Bushfire
eventsAnnotated.description: The 2013 New South Wales bushfires were a series of bushfires in Australia across the state of New South Wales primarily starting, or becoming notable, on the 13 October 2013. The user is a response officer in the command and control center for the New South Wales state in Australia. <a href='https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2013_New_South_Wales_bushfires' target='_blank'>Wikipedia Page<a>

eventsAnnotated.name: 2012 Philipinnes Flood
eventsAnnotated.description: The 2012 Luzon southwest monsoon floods were an eight-day period of torrential rain and thunderstorms in the Philippines starting on August 1, 2012. The user is a response officer in the Philippines command and control center responsible for the event. <a href='https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2012_Luzon_southwest_monsoon_floods' target='_blank'>Wikipedia Page<a>

eventsAnnotated.name: 2013 Alberta Flood
eventsAnnotated.description: The 2013 Alberta floods was a case of catastrophic flooding in Alberta, Canada triggered by continious rainfall. The user is a response officer in the command and control center for the Alberta region of Canada. <a href='https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2013_Alberta_floods' target='_blank'>Wikipedia Page<a>

eventsAnnotated.name: 2015 Nepal Earthquake
eventsAnnotated.description: The April 2015 Nepal earthquake (also known as the Gorkha earthquake) occurred at 11:56 Nepal Standard Time on 25 April, with a magnitude of 7.8Mw and a maximum Mercalli Intensity of VIII (Severe). Its epicenter  was east of Gorkha District at Barpak, Gorkha. The user is a response officer in the command and control center responsible for responding to the earthquake as it unfolds. <a href='https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/April_2015_Nepal_earthquake' target='_blank'>Wikipedia Page<a>

eventsAnnotated.name: [Split Topic - Part 2] 2015 Nepal Earthquake
eventsAnnotated.description: The April 2015 Nepal earthquake (also known as the Gorkha earthquake) occurred at 11:56 Nepal Standard Time on 25 April, with a magnitude of 7.8Mw and a maximum Mercalli Intensity of VIII (Severe). eventsAnnotated.name: [Split Topic - Part 2] 2014 Typhoon Hagupit
eventsAnnotated.description: Typhoon Hagupit, known in the Philippines as Typhoon Ruby, was the second most intense tropical cyclone in 2014. Hagupit particularly impacted the Philippines in early December while gradually weakening. The user is a response officer in the Philippines command and control center responsible for impact to the country. <a href='https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Typhoon_Hagupit_%282014%29' target='_blank'>Wikipedia Page<a>
